Platform: Windows Vista or 7
Language: VisualBasic.NET

In order to run this application, you must have the .NET framework installed.
If not, you should be able to visit the FinalProject\publish directory and execute the
setup.exe file contained within that folder. It will install the basics necessary to run
this application on your system.
That will all that is necessary to simply run this application on your system.

In order to edit the source code, it's best to visit the following site and obtain/install
the IDE used to create this project:
http://microsoft.com/express/download

In order to validate the tests, you would need to modify the source code, then recompile
the application to verify the checks are actually throwing errors if the conversions fail.
The conversions are setup in FinalProject\ConvertTest.vb. Simply modify one of the values
in the New() subprogram, recompile, rerun, then click on the test button in the GUI. You
will notice the application throwing errors when expected values differ from the calculated
values.
